laboratory_examinations.findings: Severe right spinal accessory nerve injury with ongoing denervation of the trapezius muscle.
Moderate arthritic changes at the superior aspect of the glenohumeral joint and a high-riding (superiorly subluxated) humeral head.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: At the time of final follow-up thirty months post-surgery, radiographs showed persistent high-riding humeral head.
